                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">"System Requirements
<br />
What are the game's requirements?
<br />
-Operating System: Windows 98/2000/ME/XP
<br />
-Processor: 1GHz or greater
<br />
-RAM: 512 MB
<br />
-Video Card: DirectX 9 compatible. Pixel shader and vertex shader compatible hardware with 64 MB of texture memory
<br />
-Sound Card: DirectSound compatible audio hardware" </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
With EQ1 barely runable at those specs (not to meantion rediculous for those of us in raid guilds w/ 70+ people on the screen and all effects off), they expect EQ2 to be playable? heh...
<br />
I still don't like the "Any race can be any class" Sorry, but there is no way an ogre could pas as an enchanter.  Its just not "Fantasy"  Ogres aren't capable of understanding how magic works (Healer/preist classes don't count, since their power is dirived from a "god").  Not to mention lack the charisma to possibly be able to woe mobs the way a chanter is supposed to.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=685971" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://l33tpenguin.50megs.com/arax-sig6.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
